@ctx
>>stack
> Haxe 4.3+, Eval/Node.js/C++ targets
> Pure Haxe, no external dependencies (like tink_core)
>>workflow
> maintain spec parity with official Wren
> all P0 features must pass TestWren.hx before commit
> Haxiom: Bytecode is PERMANENTLY DITCHED (only plain .hx source files with AST compilation caching are allowed)
> Haxiom: No abstracts and no generics allowed in Haxiom scripts
> Haxiom: No async/await logic or native Promise/Task systems are needed (matching native Haxe)
> Haxiom: Strict subset-of-Haxe design philosophy. No custom or non-standard language features. The learning curve focuses only on intentionally omitted features (e.g., no macros, no abstracts, no generics).
! session:start => check project.axl for focus and next_act

